page.title: 01ST. KEW PRECIS.
page.content: The area has undulating land with narrow twisty roads on the north coast of Cornwall. The main rock basis is made of granite and slate. There is quite a lot of woodland, but mainly farmland dealing with mostly grass, some cereals and mixed farming. There are two inns; one in the old village by the fifteenth century church and another in St. Kew Highway. There is a school on a hill about one and a half miles from there. In this area there are council houses and private houses. There are very few men who work in the area and live in it. There are several hamlets around the village and lots of holiday cottages. There are no sports' facilities in the village.
